This European Union Public Licence (the ‘EUPL’) applies to the Work (as defined below) which is provided under the terms of this Licence. Any use of the Work, other than as authorised under this Licence, is prohibited (authorised use includes, but is not limited to, commercial use).

The Work is provided under the terms of this Licence when the Licensor (as defined below) has placed the following notice immediately following the copyright notice for the Work:

Licensed under the EUPL

or has expressed by any other means his willingness to license under the EUPL.

1. Definitions
In this Licence, the following terms have the following meaning:
- ‘The Licence’: this Licence.
- ‘The Original Work’: the software or relevant source code, including its documentation, made available by the Licensor under the Licence.
- ‘The Work’: the Original Work and/or its Derivative Works.
- ‘Derivative Works’: the software or other material that could be created by a Licensee, based upon the Work or modifications to the Work.
- ‘The Source Code’: the human-readable form of the Work which is the most convenient for people to study or modify.
- ‘The Executable Code’: any code which has been compiled in order to be interpreted by a computer as a program.
- ‘The Licensor’: the natural or legal person who makes the Work available under the Licence.
- ‘The Licensee’: any natural or legal person who makes use of the Work under the terms of the Licence.

